subSubSection.paragraph:
Some authors considered the Small Indian Mongoose and the Javan Mongoose (H. javanicus) conspecific under the name H. javanicus or H. auropunctatus. Recent molecular studies suggest that they should be treated as separate species. Five subspecies have been recognized in H. auropunctatus, but the taxonomy needs clarification as some populations (notably from southern 
China
) have not been confirmed as belonging to this species or to H. javanicus. Included here is H. palustris, which has been considered either a separate species or a synonym of H. auropunctatus.
